  "text": "The particular chemical structure and conformation of fucoidans suggested the possibility that these polysaccharides may directly interfere with the binding of growth factors to their specific cognate receptors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Therefore, we examined the ability of each fraction to interfere with bFGF-receptor interactions on BALB/c 3T3 fibroblasts [CITATION_3] . Parent sulfated polysaccharides (L.s.-P) or the above-mentioned fractions were added separately at final concentrations of 100 mg/ml to fibroblasts suspensions on bFGF-coated plates. As shown in Figure 4C ",
